    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "85%? That's a pretty bold number given how messy the Phase II data looked last week. I noticed some pretty wild swings in the patient response rates in the raw logs. Are you sure that 85% isn't an overstatement? I don't want to go to the Board with a high confidence score only to have the next data dump tank our funding. Can you break down why you're seeing it as so stable?",
